 education and academic literacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEducation, BilingualzChinazHong Kong. 0aEducation, BilingualismzChinazHong Kong. 0aLanguage and educationzChinazHong Kong. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching (Higher)zChinazHong Kong. 0aMulticulturalismzChinazHong Kong. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aacademic biliteracies.  aacademic literacy.  aacademic reading and writing.  abilingualism.  abiliteracy.  ahigher education.  amultilingual higher education.  amultilingual.  amultilingualism.  areading for academic purposes.  atranslanguaging.  awriting for academic purposes.1 aAntia, Bassey E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaker, Beverly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCostley, Tracey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDyers, Charlyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsquinca, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGentil, Guillaume, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiller, Gwenn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodges, Rhian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHurst, Ellen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIfan, Gwawr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiernan, Julia E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadiba, Mbulungeni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMangonéz, Lauren Pérez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManu, Zina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/v